{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_015APWn2N7B1eyG4AJgmZY9w","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Diagnostics confirm a clean, robust physical picture:\n\n- **Even in the worst geometric tail** (thin SiC + small void + high burnup), net SiC tangential stress peaks at ~70 MPa (case B) — far below the 873 MPa strength. Weibull failure probability is astronomically small. **Overpressure fails ≈0 particles in every case at ≤1800 °C**, even with +30% CO and 50–75% loss of protective compression.\n- **Cs-137 diffuses through intact SiC** — this is the dominant, computable release (order 1–13%), strongly driven by temperature and time.\n- The Cs effective diffusion length is the biggest release-magnitude uncertainty (spans ~10×).\n\nLet me save the numeric record and write the calculation note."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1257,"cache_read_input_tokens":69244,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1257},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"global"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4b3d406f-4e66-44c2-8ed1-d166103fe542","uuid":"3dcfb6a2-f7e9-498d-b7cd-671ac0b0bf27","request_id":"req_011Ccdzz2aaA41HzK8SpiZPZ"}
