{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01HgyUsBdxaTxXqdUvt6HiAS","type":"tool_result","content":"total 44\ndrwxr-xr-x 2 501  staff  4096 Jul  2 22:16 .\ndrwxr-xr-x 4 501  staff  4096 Jul  2 22:06 ..\n-rw-r--r-- 1 root root   3938 Jul  2 22:14 calc_output.txt\n-rw-r--r-- 1 root root  14880 Jul  2 22:16 calculation_note.md\n-rw-r--r-- 1 root root  12920 Jul  2 22:13 triso_calc.py\n---\n213 calculation_note.md\n--- headings ---\n# Calculation note — TRISO particle failure and fission-product release under accident heating\n## 1. Physical model and correlations used\n### 1.1 What \"failure\" means and what drives it\n### 1.2 Internal pressure (pressure-vessel loading)\n### 1.3 SiC tangential stress\n### 1.4 Failure statistics\n### 1.5 Release model\n## 2. Per-case results\n### Fractional release predictions\n## 3. Why over-pressure fails essentially no particles (the key quantitative finding)\n## 4. What could still fail particles at 1800 °C (A2, B), and the small non-zero counts\n## 5. Ranking — which case suffers most, and the T/burnup sensitivities\n## 6. Assumptions and confidence\n## 7. One-line summary per case","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4b3d406f-4e66-44c2-8ed1-d166103fe542","uuid":"639774cd-b0e3-415a-b01a-aa2e34da23ab","timestamp":"2026-07-02T22:16:30.513Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"total 44\ndrwxr-xr-x 2 501  staff  4096 Jul  2 22:16 .\ndrwxr-xr-x 4 501  staff  4096 Jul  2 22:06 ..\n-rw-r--r-- 1 root root   3938 Jul  2 22:14 calc_output.txt\n-rw-r--r-- 1 root root  14880 Jul  2 22:16 calculation_note.md\n-rw-r--r-- 1 root root  12920 Jul  2 22:13 triso_calc.py\n---\n213 calculation_note.md\n--- headings ---\n# Calculation note — TRISO particle failure and fission-product release under accident heating\n## 1. Physical model and correlations used\n### 1.1 What \"failure\" means and what drives it\n### 1.2 Internal pressure (pressure-vessel loading)\n### 1.3 SiC tangential stress\n### 1.4 Failur